; type=&quot;math/mml&quot;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&quot;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&quot;&gt;&lt;mi&gt;α&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;=&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mfrac&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;d&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mi&gt;ω&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;d&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mi&gt;t&lt;merror&gt;&lt;mtext&gt;Unknown node type: span&lt;/mtext&gt;&lt;/merror&gt;&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;/mfrac&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/script&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;script id=&quot;MathJax-Element-24&quot; type=&quot;math/mml&quot;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&quot;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&quot;&gt;&lt;mi&gt;α&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;=&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mfrac&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;d&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mi&gt;ω&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;d&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mi&gt;t&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; text-transform: none; word-spacing: normal;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;where&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;/mfrac&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/script&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;MathJax_Math-italic&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 17.08px; text-wrap-mode: nowrap;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&amp;alpha; = &amp;Delta;&amp;omega; / &amp;Delta;t.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The SI unit of angular acceleration is rad/sec&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Angular acceleration is a vector quantity, having both magnitude and direction.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;It plays a crucial role in rotational dynamics, helping to describe how quickly an object accelerates or decelerates in its rotational motion.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Strain:&lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Strain is a dimensionless quantity representing the deformation of a material relative to its original dimensions.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It is mathematically expressed as the ratio of change in length to the original length .&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Angular velocity:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Angular velocity is defined as the rate at which an object rotates or revolves around a central point.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Its dimensional formula is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;M&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;position: relative;  line-height: 0; vertical-align: baseline; top: -0.5em;font-size:10.5px;&quot;&gt;0&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;L&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;position: relative;  line-height: 0; vertical-align: baseline; top: -0.5em;font-size:10.5px;&quot;&gt;0&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;T&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;position: relative;  line-height: 0; vertical-align: baseline; top: -0.5em;font-size:10.5px;&quot;&gt;-1&lt;/span&gt;, and the SI unit is rad/sec.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Frequency:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Frequency refers to the number of occurrences of a repeating event per unit time.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Its dimensional formula is &lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;M&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;position: relative;  line-height: 0; vertical-align: baseline; top: -0.5em;font-size:10.5px;&quot;&gt;0&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;L&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;position: relative;  line-height: 0; vertical-align: baseline; top: -0.5em;font-size:10.5px;&quot;&gt;0&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;T&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;position: relative;  line-height: 0; vertical-align: baseline; top: -0.5em;font-size:10.5px;&quot;&gt;-1&lt;/span&gt;, and the SI unit is Hz.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Rotational Dynamics:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Rotational dynamics deals with the motion of objects that rotate about a fixed axis.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Key parameters include angular displacement, angular velocity, angular acceleration, and torque.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
